  the area also gives its name to :    gare montparnasse : trains to brittany , tgv to rennes , tours , bordeaux , le mans ; rebuilt as a modern tgv station ;   the large montparnasse – bienvenüe métro station ;   cimetière du montparnasse : the montparnasse cemetery , where charles baudelaire , constantin brâncuși , jean - paul sartre , simone de beauvoir , samuel beckett , and susan sontag are buried   tour montparnasse , a lone skyscraper   the pasteur institute is located in the area .

